  <answer fraction="0" format="html"><text><![CDATA[\(3x^{-1}\)]]></text><feedback format="html"><text></text></feedback></answer>
  <answer fraction="0" format="html"><text><![CDATA[\(3x\)]]></text><feedback format="html"><text></text></feedback></answer>
</question>
<!-- Q5 --><question type="multichoice">
  <name><text>ODE - Reduction of Order</text></name>
  <questiontext format="html"><text><![CDATA[<p>If \(y_1\) is a known solution of \(y''+p(x)y'+q(x)y=0\), the second solution via reduction of order \(y_2=v(x)y_1\) satisfies (for \(v'=u\)):</p>]]></text></questiontext>
  <generalfeedback format="html"><text><![CDATA[<p><strong>Answer: (C) \(u'+\left(\frac{2y_1'}{y_1}+p\right)u=0\)</strong></p><p>Substituting \(y=vy_1\): \(v''y_1+2v'y_1'+vy_1''+p(v'y_1+vy_1')+qvy_1=0\). Since \(y_1''+py_1'+qy_1=0\): \(y_1v''+v'(2y_1'+py_1)=0\). Setting \(u=v'\): \(u'+(2y_1'/y_1+p)u=0\), a first-order linear ODE for \(u\). Solution: \(u=\frac{c}{y_1^2}e^{-\int p\,dx}\) (Abel's formula).</p>]]></text></generalfeedback>
  <defaultgrade>1.0</defaultgrade><penalty>0.25</penalty><hidden>0</hidden>
  <single>true</small><shuffleanswers>true</shuffleanswers><answernumbering>abc</answernumbering>
  <answer fraction="0" format="html"><text><![CDATA[\(u'-pu=0\)]]></text><feedback format="html"><text></text></feedback></answer>
  <answer fraction="0" format="html"><text><![CDATA[\(u''+pu'+qu=0\)]]></text><feedback format="html"><text></text></feedback></answer>
  <answer fraction="100" format="html"><text><![CDATA[\(u'+\!\left(\dfrac{2y_1'}{y_1}+p\right)u=0\)]]></text><feedback format="html"><text></text></feedback></answer>
  <answer fraction="0" format="html"><text><![CDATA[\(y_1 u''+pu'=0\)]]></text><feedback format="html"><text></text></feedback></answer>
</question>
<!-- Q6 --><question type="multichoice">
  <name><text>ODE - Variation of Parameters</text></name>
  <questiontext format="html"><text><![CDATA[<p>For the ODE \(y''+y=\sec x\), the particular solution via variation of parameters is:</p>]]></text></questiontext>
  <generalfeedback format="html"><text><![CDATA[<p><strong>Answer: (A) \(y_p=x\sin x+\cos x\ln|\cos x|\)</strong></p><p>Homogeneous: \(y_1=\cos x, y_2=\sin x\), \(W=1\). Variation of parameters: \(u_1'=-y_2f/W=-\sin x\sec x=-\tan x\Rightarrow u_1=\ln|\cos x|\). \(u_2'=y_1f/W=\cos x\sec x=1\Rightarrow u_2=x\). Particular: \(y_p=u_1y_1+u_2y_2=\cos x\ln|\cos x|+x\sin x\).</p>]]></text></generalfeedback>
  <defaultgrade>1.0</defaultgrade><penalty>0.25</penalty><hidden>0</hidden>
  <single>true</single><shuffleanswers>true</shuffleanswers><answernumbering>abc</answernumbering>
  <answer fraction="100" format="html"><text><![CDATA[\(y_p=x\sin x+\cos x\ln|\cos x|\)]]></text><feedback format="html"><text></text></feedback></answer>
  <answer fraction="0" format="html"><text><![CDATA[\(y_p=x\cos x\)]]></text><feedback format="html"><text></text></feedback></answer>
  <answer fraction="0" format="html"><text><![CDATA[\(y_p=\sin x\ln|\sin x|\)]]></text><feedback format="html"><text></text></feedback></answer>
  <answer fraction="0" format="html"><text><![CDATA[\(y_p=\cos x\sec x\)]]></text><feedback format="html"><text></text></feedback></answer>
</question>
<!-- Q7 --><question type="multichoice">
  <name><text>ODE - Characteristic Equation</text></name>
  <questiontext format="html"><text><![CDATA[<p>The general solution of \(y''-5y'+6y=0\) is:</p>]]></text></questiontext>
  <generalfeedback format="html"><text><![CDATA[<p><strong>Answer: (B) \(y=c_1e^{2x}+c_2e^{3x}\)</strong></p><p>Characteristic equation: \(r^2-5r+6=0\Rightarrow(r-2)(r-3)=0\Rightarrow r=2,3\). General solution: \(y=c_1e^{2x}+c_2e^{3x}\). For distinct real roots \(r_1,r_2\): \(y=c_1e^{r_1x}+c_2e^{r_2x}\).</p>]]></text></generalfeedback>
  <defaultgrade>1.0</defaultgrade><penalty>0.25</penalty><hidden>0</hidden>
  <single>true</single><shuffleanswers>true</shuffleanswers><answernumbering>abc</answernumbering>
  <answer fraction="0" format="html"><text><![CDATA[\(y=(c_1+c_2x)e^{5x/2}\)]]></text><feedback format="html"><text></text></feedback></answer>
  <answer fraction="100" format="html"><text><![CDATA[\(y=c_1e^{2x}+c_2e^{3x}\)]]></text><feedback format="html"><text></text></feedback></answer>
  <answer fraction="0" format="html"><text><![CDATA[\(y=c_1e^{-2x}+c_2e^{-3x}\)]]></text><feedback format="html"><text></text></feedback></answer>
  <answer fraction="0" format="html"><text><![CDATA[\(y=e^{5x/2}(c_1\cos x+c_2\sin x)\)]]></text><feedback format="html"><text></text></feedback></answer>
</question>
<!-- Q8 --><question type="multichoice">
  <name><text>ODE - Complex Roots</text></name>
  <questiontext format="html"><text><![CDATA[<p>The general solution of \(y''+4y=0\) is:</p>]]></text></questiontext>
  <generalfeedback format="html"><text><![CDATA[<p><strong>Answer: (C) \(y=c_1\cos 2x+c_2\sin 2x\)</strong></p><p>Characteristic equation: \(r^2+4=0\Rightarrow r=\pm2i\). For complex roots \(\alpha\pm i\beta\): \(y=e^{\alpha x}(c_1\cos\beta x+c_2\sin\beta x)\). Here \(\alpha=0,\beta=2\): \(y=c_1\cos2x+c_2\sin2x\). This is simple harmonic motion with angular frequency 2.</p>]]></text></generalfeedback>
  <defaultgrade>1.0</defaultgrade><penalty>0.25</penalty><hidden>0</hidden>
  <single>true</single><shuffleanswers>true</shuffleanswers><answernumbering>abc</answernumbering>
  <answer fraction="0" format="html"><text><![CDATA[\(y=c_1e^{2x}+c_2e^{-2x}\)]]></text><feedback format="html"><text></text></feedback></answer>
  <answer fraction="0" format="html"><text><![CDATA[\(y=e^{2x}(c_1+c_2x)\)]]></text><feedback format="html"><text></text></feedback></answer>
  <answer fraction="100" format="html"><text><![CDATA[\(y=c_1\cos2x+c_2\sin2x\)]]></text><feedback format="html"><text></text></feedback></answer>
  <answer fraction="0" format="html"><text><![CDATA[\(y=c_1e^{2ix}+c_2e^{-2ix}\)]]></text><feedback format="html"><text></text></feedback></answer>
</question>
<!-- Q9 --><question type="multichoice">
  <name><text>ODE - Repeated Roots</text></name>
  <questiontext format="html"><text><![CDATA[<p>The general solution of \(y''-2y'+y=0\) is:</p>]]></text></questiontext>
  <generalfeedback format="html"><text><![CDATA[<p><strong>Answer: (A) \(y=(c_1+c_2x)e^x\)</strong></p><p>Characteristic equation: \(r^2-2r+1=(r-1)^2=0\Rightarrow r=1\) (double root). For repeated root \(r\): \(y=(c_1+c_2x)e^{rx}\). Here: \(y=(c_1+c_2x)e^x\). The second solution \(xe^x\) is found by reduction of order or by the general formula for repeated roots.</p>]]></text></generalfeedback>
  <defaultgrade>1.0</defaultgrade><penalty>0.25</penalty><hidden>0</hidden>
  <single>true</single><shuffleanswers>true</shuffleanswers><answernumbering>abc</answernumbering>
  <answer fraction="100" format="html"><text><![CDATA[\(y=(c_1+c_2x)e^x\)]]></text><feedback format="html"><text></text></feedback></answer>
  <answer fraction="0" format="html"><text><![CDATA[\(y=c_1e^x+c_2e^{-x}\)]]></text><feedback format="html"><text></text></feedback></answer>
  <answer fraction="0" format="html"><text><![CDATA[\(y=(c_1+c_2x^2)e^x\)]]></text><feedback format="html"><text></text></feedback></answer>
  <answer fraction="0" format="html"><text><![CDATA[\(y=c_1\cos x+c_2\sin x\)]]></text><feedback format="html"><text></text></feedback></answer>
</question>
<!-- Q10 --><question type="multichoice">
  <name><text>ODE - Undetermined Coefficients</text></name>
  <questiontext format="html"><text><![CDATA[<p>The particular solution of \(y''-3y'+2y=e^{3x}\) is of the form:</p>]]></text></questiontext>
  <generalfeedback format="html"><text><![CDATA[<p><strong>Answer: (B) \(y_p=Ae^{3x}\)</strong></p><p>Since \(e^{3x}\) is not a solution of the homogeneous equation (roots are 1 and 2, not 3), we try \(y_p=Ae^{3x}\). Substituting: \(9A-9A+2A=2A=1\Rightarrow A=1/2\). Particular solution: \(y_p=\frac{1}{2}e^{3x}\).</p>]]></text></generalfeedback>
