<!-- Q16 --><question type="multichoice">
  <name><text>ODE - Resonance</text></name>
  <questiontext format="html"><text><![CDATA[<p>The particular solution of \(y''+\omega^2y=\cos\omega x\) exhibits resonance. Its form is:</p>]]></text></questiontext>
  <generalfeedback format="html"><text><![CDATA[<p><strong>Answer: (B) \(y_p=\frac{x}{2\omega}\sin\omega x\)</strong></p><p>Since \(\cos\omega x\) solves the homogeneous equation, the usual trial fails. We multiply by \(x\): try \(y_p=x(A\cos\omega x+B\sin\omega x)\). Substituting (or using undetermined coefficients with modification): \(A=0, B=1/(2\omega)\). Particular solution: \(y_p=\frac{x}{2\omega}\sin\omega x\). Amplitude grows linearly — resonance phenomenon.</p>]]></text></generalfeedback>
