</question>
<!-- Q20 --><question type="multichoice">
  <name><text>ODE - CSIR Style</text></name>
  <questiontext format="html"><text><![CDATA[<p>The ODE \(4x^2y''+4xy'-y=0\) for \(x>0\): its indicial equation has roots \(m=\):</p>]]></text></questiontext>
  <generalfeedback format="html"><text><![CDATA[<p><strong>Answer: (B) \(m=1/2\) and \(m=-1/2\)</strong></p><p>Substituting \(y=x^m\): \(4x^2m(m-1)x^{m-2}+4xmx^{m-1}-x^m=x^m[4m(m-1)+4m-1]=x^m[4m^2-1]=0\). Indicial equation: \(4m^2-1=0\Rightarrow m=\pm1/2\). General solution: \(y=c_1x^{1/2}+c_2x^{-1/2}=c_1\sqrt{x}+c_2/\sqrt{x}\).</p>]]></text></generalfeedback>
